Download residue removal scope — confirming before I touch files.

Plan says: remove Op::SaveAsset variant, `assets` table in sqlite.rs, and save_asset from Storage trait. But save_asset + AssetKind download path is interwoven well beyond those three points:

1. `src/storage/mod.rs`            → Storage::save_asset trait method
2. `src/storage/sqlite.rs`         → Op::SaveAsset + `assets` table + impl
3. `src/storage/filesystem.rs`     → save_asset impl (atomic write, sidecar JSON)
4. `src/download/` (mod.rs + pipeline.rs) → AssetKind (Image/Pdf/...), DownloadPolicy, size helpers
5. `src/crawler.rs` (~770-835)     → classify + should_store + save_asset + ArtifactSaved emit + DecisionMade size-exceeded
6. `src/config.rs`                 → Config.download_policy field + default
7. `src/cli/mod.rs` (672)          → CLI `--download-kinds` / `--max-download-size` parse
8. `src/cli/args.rs` (~126)        → CLI arg struct fields for --follow-all-assets etc
9. `src/lib.rs`                    → `pub mod download;`

ArtifactSaved EventKind variant stays (used by script/captures).

Plan says "Se algo do download residual (SaveAsset) estiver entrelaçado com infra legítima, perguntar via IPC antes de deletar." — isso aqui está entrelaçado.

Minha leitura: remover TUDO da lista acima (1–9 menos ArtifactSaved), já que "trilhos: antibot, browser control, spa/pwa, artifacts, scale" — download binário genérico (PDF/image/media/archive/document) não é nenhum deles, foi a 4.4 cancelada. Script captures permanece porque emite ArtifactSaved via outro caminho (não via Storage::save_asset).

